Roe GILLESPIE v. ABEGG & REINHOLD COMPANY, Limited. No. 4751. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Oct. 5, 1953. P. H. Winn, Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellant. Kerr, Lambert, Conn & Roberts, Ada, Okl., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and MURRAH, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed on motion of appellee for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
